      • lastNGroupByKey

        KvFilterSource lastNGroupByKey(KeySource keySource,
                             int n)
        On first partition sources all keys from keySource. As KvFilter accepts only first N rows per key. Because rows are fed in last-to-first, first N for KvFilter means last N chronologically. All keys with -1 rowID are re-sourced for next partition.
        Parameters:
        keySource - the KeySource for first partition
        n - number of rows per key value to accept.
        Returns:
        KvFilterSource instance for wiring.

      • lastNGroupByKey

        KvFilterSource lastNGroupByKey(KeySource keySource,
                             int n,
                             RowFilter filter)
        On first partition sources all keys from keySource. As KvFilter accepts only first N rows per key that match filter. Because rows are fed in last-to-first, first N for KvFilter means last N chronologically. All keys with -1 rowID are re-sourced for next partition.
        Parameters:
        keySource - the KeySource for first partition
        n - number of rows per key value to accept.
        Returns:
        KvFilterSource instance for wiring.
